    "To address these challenges, the proposed McNeRF uses two techniques: multi-camera alignment and brightness-consistent rendering.",
    "Multi-camera alignment.",
    "Autonomous vehicles, despite having a localization module for accurate camera poses, face challenges with asynchronous trigger times across multiple cameras.",
    "To align camera extrinsics for NeRF training, our core idea is to leverage a consistent spatial coordinate system provided by Agisoft Metashape [2] to align the images captured by multiple cameras at different timestamps.",
    "Specifically, let I (i,k) and ξ (i,k) be the image captured by the ith camera at the kth trigger and the corresponding camera pose in the vehicle's global coordinate space, respectively."
